<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1438,1335,2034]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,215]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Male: Head exposed, interocular space 
<quantity box="[671,762,1634,1660]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
less than the distance between antennal sockets (
<quantity box="[1356,1427,1634,1660]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
) (
<figureCitation box="[160,233,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[216,233,1672,1698]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
); antennae three-fourths as long as body (
<figureCitation box="[733,805,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[789,805,1672,1698]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); maxillary palpomeres short, the fourth shorter than the third and almost as long as the fifth. Pronotum transverse, elliptical, wider than long; anterior margin with cephalic section fissured on each side of the supra-cephalic portion of the disk (bifissate), separating the disk from the wing-like lateral sections of the pronotum, fissures V shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1116,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Figs. 6, 8</figureCitation>
). Tegmina and wings fully developed, extending beyond margin of abdomen; hindwings complete; cubitus with incomplete branches. Antero-ventral margin of front femur unarmed, 
<typeStatus box="[781,837,1858,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
D; tarsal segments with pulvilli, tarsal claws symmetrical, unspecialized, arolia present. Supra-anal plate transverse, bilobate, apico-lateral margin rounded, posterior margin with V-shaped mesad emargination (
<figureCitation box="[921,1013,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[979,1013,1933,1959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); right paraproct hook-shaped, left paraproct entire (
<figureCitation box="[353,426,1970,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[409,426,1970,1996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate slightly asymmetrical, styles simple (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1176,1970,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[1145,1176,1970,1996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Genitalia as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,231,2008,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14</number>
</figureCitation>
: left phallomere (L 
<number box="[467,478,2008,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
) with a characteristic heavily sclerotized cleft (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1147,2008,2034]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[1114,1147,2008,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
), hook on the right side (R 
<number box="[181,196,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
) with a preapical incision (
<figureCitation box="[522,610,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[578,610,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
), median phallomere (L 
<number box="[897,911,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
