<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
