).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293972/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" targetBox="[159,1424,252,1279]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1303,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,361,1303,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">FIGURES 15–18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[370,680,1303,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Schistopeltis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microschistos" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[370,680,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Schistopeltis microschistos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[688,753,1303,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[688,753,1303,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female paratype: 15, pronotum (dorsal) with black arrows indicating fissure variation between the sexes; 16, habitus (dorsal); 17, supra-anal plate and cerci (dorsal); 18, subgenital plate (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissure.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1431,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Color: General dorsal coloration beige. Pronotum margins finely outlined with black, thicker on caudallateral angles; disk with two black spots (
<figureCitation box="[646,761,1467,1493]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Figs. 6, 8</figureCitation>
). Head dark chestnut; clypeus and labrum pale chestnut; areas adjacent to antennal sockets pale yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[746,818,1503,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[801,818,1503,1529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tegmina beige, with blackish maculae on the base of the subcosta area and anal (plical) vein; discoidal field veins blackish brown with maculae (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1420,1539,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[1402,1420,1539,1565]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Exposed mesonotal area between tegmina dark chestnut. Abdominal terga chestnut with beige lateral margins and black tubercles; abdominal sterna chestnut. Legs chestnut; tibia I–II bicolored (chestnut and beige). Supra-anal plate pale chestnut, darker along the midline; cerci with two terminal segments white (
<figureCitation box="[1298,1385,1647,1673]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 14" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,198,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,173,1817]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 14. Schistopeltis spp.: 4, Schistopeltis peculiaris Rehn, male holotype from Brazil, pronotum (dorsal). 5, Schistopeltis lizeri Rehn, male holotype from Bolivia, pronotum (dorsal). 6 – 14, Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp.: 6 – 8, male holotype: 6, pronotum (dorsal); 7, head; 8, habitus (dorsal); 9 – 14, male paratype: 9, paraprocts (rp: right, lp: left); 10, supra-anal plate (sa) and cerci (c) (dorsal); 11, subgenital plate (sg) and styles (s) (ventral); 12, first genital sclerite of left phallomere L 1 (dorsal); 13, median sclerite L 2 vm, L 2 d (dorsal); 14, hooked sclerite of right phallomere R 2 (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissures." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293971/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[1352,1385,1647,1673]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1431,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Female differing from male in size (see measurements), shape and color of supra-anal and subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[238,383,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,276,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,252,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,250,1289]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp., female paratype: 15, pronotum (dorsal) with black arrows indicating fissure variation between the sexes; 16, habitus (dorsal); 17, supra-anal plate and cerci (dorsal); 18, subgenital plate (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissure." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293972/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
), shallower pronotal fissures (
<figureCitation box="[747,836,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,276,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,252,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,250,1289]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp., female paratype: 15, pronotum (dorsal) with black arrows indicating fissure variation between the sexes; 16, habitus (dorsal); 17, supra-anal plate and cerci (dorsal); 18, subgenital plate (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissure." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293972/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[804,836,1719,1745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), and shape of maculae on pronotum and tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[159,302,1755,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,276,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,252,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,250,1289]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. Schistopeltis microschistos n. sp., female paratype: 15, pronotum (dorsal) with black arrows indicating fissure variation between the sexes; 16, habitus (dorsal); 17, supra-anal plate and cerci (dorsal); 18, subgenital plate (ventral). Arrows indicate pronotal fissure." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293972/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Figs. 15, 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
